🕒 Digital Clock

A simple Digital Clock built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
It displays the current time in HH:MM:SS format and updates automatically every second.

🚀 Features

⏰ Real-time digital clock

🔄 Updates every second using setInterval()

🎨 Styled with card layout and purple theme

📱 Responsive design with Flexbox

✨ Clean and minimal UI

🛠️ Technologies Used

HTML5 – Structure

CSS3 – Styling (Flexbox, card design, shadows)

JavaScript (ES6) – Clock functionality

📸 Preview

(Add a screenshot of your project here once you take one 📷)

📂 Project Structure
digital-clock/
│── index.html     # Main HTML file  
│── style.css      # Styling file  
│── scripts.js     # Clock logic (JavaScript)  

⚡ How It Works

Uses JavaScript’s Date() object to get the current hours, minutes, and seconds.

Adds a leading 0 if values are below 10 for proper formatting (e.g., 07 instead of 7).

Updates the DOM every second with setInterval().

📌 Future Improvements

Add AM/PM format option

Include Dark/Light Mode toggle

Display Day & Date

